snippet.textDisplay: Uaaaaah, That last bit sent me back in time cringing. I remember when I was 16 or 17 I went with my best friend and his dad to a greek restaurant. It was fully seated and they wanted us to turn away. There was one visibly empty table and my friends dad asked about it. They told us that it was reserved in 45 minutes and his dad told them that we would be finished by then. The waitress said okden. So we sat down and ordered real quick. While we ate my friends dad chugged one Ouzo after another. We finished on time but when the waitress came to pick up the tab the dad started to insisting that we needed to get a dessert (and he wanted another Ouzo). Me and my friend looked at each other in embarrassed panic. And while he argued with the waitress we saw the guys who obviously ordered the table come in. It was hell
